  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><p class="style1">Over the next few days we will be reviewing Shari's Time and Attendance policies. We will also be looking at different reports that help us manage labor. Today we will begin this process by reading about entering new employees into the POS system. </p>
    <p class="style1">At Shari's we use the POS system to transfer information about the store and it's employees into RAS (Restaurant Automation System). RAS transfers this information to the corporate office in a format that can be used by other systems for generating reports, payroll checks and employee history.</p>
    <p class="style1">In your purple POS manual turn to the Time and Attendance chapter and read pages 1-11. After reading go to your store computer and click on &quot;EmpEntry Train&quot; from either the icon (a pencil) on the desk top or from the start menu. The password for this program is 1, then click enter. You will know that you are in the training format if the screen background is blue. Complete the following list of items. Check off each item as completed and then fax it to your instructor.</p>    </td>
  </tr>
